5000|$|Crataegus azarolus is {{a species}} of {{hawthorn}} known by the common names azarole, azerole, and <b>Mediterranean</b> <b>medlar.</b> It is native to the Mediterranean Basin and is a common plant there, growing on sites comparable to those the European common hawthorn grows on. In the Arab countries it is the commonest of the hawthorn species; in the Arabic language the term [...] "common hawthorn" [...] means the azarole hawthorn. When growing in the wild the azerole bears plentiful crops of haw fruits, which {{are similar to the}} haws of the European common hawthorn, but plumper.|$|E
